MS in Computer Science in the USA: Top Universities, Eligibility, Scholarship, Jobs for Indian Students

  • 270 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 23,2023 05:47 PM IST

Every day, new technology and innovations shape our world. Pursuing an MS in Computer Science is a fantastic opportunity for Indian students to develop their skills and expertise in this vibrant field. Read the blog to learn why the USA is an excellent choice for a master's in computer science and know more about the top universities, scholarships and jobs for Indian students.

As technology advancements, the demand for qualified computer science experts increases. The USA is a home to the best colleges and research organizations, making it a popular choice for students pursuing an MS in Computer Science. With an extreme focus on innovation and creativity, these universities provide students with complete education that prepares them to succeed in their professions.

Studying in the USA also exposes students to global work cultures, modern research facilities, and an extensive educational environment, which can considerably improve a student's job prospects. This blog will provide brief information about the best universities for (Masters) MS in Computer science in the USA with eligibility criteria, scholarships and jobs for Indian students.

What is a Master in Computer Science?

Master (MS) in Computer Science is a graduate-level program that provides advanced knowledge and research in computer science field. The degree includes algorithms, data structures, robotics, software engineering and artificial intelligence coursework. The program duration is 1-2 years, depending on the program student chooses in the specific university. These skills are required to gain knowledge and to pursue a career in technology, including data analysis, cybersecurity, software development and many more.

Click to learn more about Master's programs in the USA.

Benefits of pursuing MS in Computer Science in the USA:

Acquiring a Master's in Computer Science in the USA has various advantages based on the country's world-class colleges and different learning environments. Here are some of the benefits:

  • World-class education:
    Many internationally renowned institutions in the USA provide high-quality computer science programs. Universities in the US provide students with an exceptional learning experience.
  • Research Opportunities:
    Universities in the USA are well known for their research facilities. Students can work on modern technologies such as Artificial Intelligence, Data Science and more.
  • Various Professions:
    Master's programs in the USA provides students with a wide selection of specializations that allows them to select and focus on the areas of interest most relevant to their career aspirations.
  • Professional Opportunities:
    After completing a degree, international students have several options to work in the USA for a specific period, providing valuable work experience.

Eligibility Criteria - MS in Computer Science in the USA:

To be eligible for admission to a Masters in Computer Science program in the USA, international students must meet specific requirements. The requirement can vary from program to program of any particular university:

1. Students must hold a bachelor's degree in computer science or a related subject from a recognized institution. Some colleges may admit students with non-computer science backgrounds, provided they have completed appropriate coursework or have professional experience in the field.
2. The universities set a minimum GPA or percentage. This falls typically between 3.0 to 4.0, equal to 60% to 75%.
3. Applicant must have a minimum score on English language tests such as IELTS, TOEFL or PTE.
4. Competitive GRE /GMAT scores are also accepted. It depends on the university and program students desires to choose.

Documents Required:
There are some other documents which are also required to process the application:

  • Academic transcript
  • LOR (Letter of Recommendation)   
  • SOP (Statement of Purpose)
  • Passport copy
  • English Test Scores such as IELTS, PTE or TOEFL
  •  Work experience (if necessary)
  •  Payment receipt
  •  Proof of funds

Checking all the requirements and documents before applying to a specific university is necessary.

Application Process - MS in Computer Science in the USA:

To be qualified to receive the MS in Computer Science in the USA, carefully follow the admission steps outlined below:

  • Research universities and programs of interest.
  • Taking note of specific admission requirements, deadlines, and application fees.
  • Most universities in the USA accept online applications through their websites.
  • Ensure the applicant has all the documents to submit while processing the application.
  • After applying, students should often check their email and the university's application portal.
  • As a part of the admissions process, universities may require additional documents or conduct interviews.
  • Once admitted, students must obtain a student visa (F-1 or J-1) to study in the USA.

Conclusion:
Pursuing a Master of Science (MS) in Computer Science in the USA can be a life-changing experience for Indian students, providing them with a world-class education, exposure to innovative studies, and fantastic job possibilities. Visit the nearest Canam office or book a virtual counselling session with our study abroad expert counsellors to study in the USA and navigate the journey towards an MS in Computer Science in the USA.

FAQ

Are any scholarships offered for international students wishing to pursue an (MS) Master's degree in computer science in the USA?
Several universities offer scholarships to Indian students, which reduces their financial burden of fee and other expenses.
Do international students obtain jobs in the USA after graduating?
After graduating, students can apply for (Optional Practical Training) OPT to find a job.
How long does completing the MS in Computer Science in the USA take?
Usually, the program is 1-2 years long, depending on the program and the university applicants wish to pursue.
Which exam is required for an MS in computer science in the USA?
English tests such as IELTS, TOEFL and PTE are needed. Most universities in the USA also accept GRE/GMAT scores depending on the program's requirements.
Who can be admitted to MS in Computer Science in the USA?
Applicants with bachelor's degrees in related fields are eligible for MS in Computer Science program. Eligibility criteria for this program depends on the university application process.
